ry of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally the name of the god of thunder in Norse mythology, Thor (Old Norse <i>Þórr</i>). It was not used as a personal name during the Middle Ages. The modern name is either a late 18th-century revival of the god's name or else a vernacular development of   Tord ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thor","meanings":["Originally the name of the god of thunder in Norse mythology, Thor (Old Norse <i>Þórr</i>). It was not used as a personal name during the Middle Ages. The modern name is either a late 18th-century revival of the god's name or else a vernacular development of   Tord ."]}]},{"name":"Elena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , now used quite frequently in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor or Elena Strongbow was born about 1300, her father, Sir Gilbert Strongbow, was 21 and her mother, Alice Elizabeth Garnon, was 17. She had at least 1 son with Edward Stradling. She was buried in St Donats, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1300–1385":"umbes 1300–1385","1300–1385":"1300–1385","1295–1363":"1295–1363","1318–1394":"1318–1394","1280–1367":"1280–1367","1285–1366":"1285–1366","1385":"1385","1363":"1363","1285":"1285","1394":"1394","1295":"1295","1363 ":"1363","1280":"1280","1316":"1316","1367":"1367","1366":"1366","1300":"1300","about 1367":"umbes 1367","about 1300":"umbes 1300","about 1366":"umbes 1366","1318":"1318","Caldicot, Monmouthshire, England":"Caldicot, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","St Donats, Glamorgan, Wales":"St Donats, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","St Donat's Castle, Glamorgans, Wales":"Saint Donats, Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1300–1385":"noin 1300–1385","1300–1385":"1300–1385","1295–1363":"1295–1363","1318–1394":"1318–1394","1280–1367":"1280–1367","1285–1366":"1285–1366","1385":"1385","1363":"1363","